# JobHop — Unified Recruitment & Workforce Management System
# Cursor Project Rules (.cursorrules)
# MVP — Optimized for fastest launch

## Project Overview
JobHop is a unified recruitment and workforce management platform for freelance on-demand workers in Singapore. 3 apps, 1 shared backend:

1. **Worker App** (React Native / Expo) — Mobile app for gig workers
2. **Recruiter Portal** (Next.js) — Web app for recruiters to place candidates + earn commission
3. **Agency Portal** (Next.js) — Web app for agencies/clients to manage shifts, timesheets, billing

All workers are **freelance independent contractors** — no CPF, no employment relationship. MOM (Ministry of Manpower) work eligibility must be verified before any worker can access jobs.

## Challenge Context
MCI Career Services / IMDA Open Innovation Challenge:
"Unified Recruitment and Workforce Management System for On-Demand Workers"

---

## Tech Stack (MVP)

### Frontend
- **Worker App**: React Native + Expo SDK 52 (Expo Router)
- **Recruiter Portal**: Next.js 15 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Agency Portal**: Next.js 15 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui

### Backend (single API inside Agency app)
- **API**: Next.js API Routes at `apps/agency/app/api/`
- **Database**: PostgreSQL via Supabase (Singapore region)
- **ORM**: Prisma
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth (phone OTP for workers, email/password for recruiter/agency)
- **File Storage**: Supabase Storage (NRIC uploads, student pass photos)
- **Real-time**: Supabase Realtime

### Infrastructure
- **Web**: Vercel (both Next.js apps as separate projects)
- **Mobile**: Expo EAS builds
- **Accounts**: Supabase ✅ Vercel ✅

### Architecture: Agency app hosts `/api/*`. Recruiter Portal + Worker App both call the same API. One codebase for API, one deployment, one DB connection.

